- **Title:** Carrick Therapeutics Announces First Patient Dosed in Phase 1 Clinical Trial of CT7439 (CDK12/13 Inhibitor) :: Carrick Therapeutics, Inc.  
  - **URL:** `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase`  
  - **Direct quote snippets:**  
    - “Phase 1 clinical trial evaluating **CT7439**, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (**CDK12/13**) inhibitor / **Cyclin-K glue-degrader**.”  
    - “Clinical trial details can also be found on www.clinicaltrials.gov under study ID: **NCT06600789**.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase?utm_source=openai))

- **Title:** Carrick Therapeutics Announces U.S. FDA Clearance of IND for CT7439, a First-In-Class Inhibitor of CDK12/13 :: Carrick Therapeutics, Inc.  
  - **URL:** `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/20/carrick-therapeutics-announces-u-s-fda-clearance-of-ind`  
  - **Direct quote snippets:**  
    - “**CT7439**, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (**CDK12/13**) inhibitor.”  
    - “The Company plans to initiate the **Phase 1** clinical trial in the first half of 2024… including **breast**, ovarian and Ewing's Sarcoma.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/20/carrick-therapeutics-announces-u-s-fda-clearance-of-ind?utm_source=openai))

- **Title:** CDK12/13 Inhibitor :: Carrick Therapeutics, Inc. (Pipeline page)  
  - **URL:** `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/pipeline/cdk1213-inhibitor`  
  - **Direct quote snippets:**  
    - “**CT7439: CDK12/13 inhibitor/Cyclin-K Degrader**”  
    - “The compound acts as an inhibitor of **CDK12** but also as a ‘**glue degrader**’ of **Cyclin-K**…” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/pipeline/cdk1213-inhibitor?utm_source=openai))

- **Title:** Non-enzymatic SETD1A activity drives breast cancer cell proliferation via cyclin K | *Breast Cancer Research*  
  - **URL:** `https://breast-cancer-research.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s13058-025-02101-x`  
  - **Direct quote snippets:**  
    - “**CT7439**, a dual inhibitor of **CDK12/13** and a **cyclin K glue degrader**, is now in phase I/II clinical trial… (**NCT06600789**).”  
    - “We also used **CR8**, another **cyclin K degrader**…” ([breast-cancer-research.biomedcentral.com](https://breast-cancer-research.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s13058-025-02101-x?utm_source=openai))

- **Title:** Therapeutic Targeting of CDK12/CDK13 in Triple-Negative Breast Cancer - PubMed  
  - **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/`  
  - **Direct quote snippets:**  
    - “development of **SR-4835**, a highly selective dual inhibitor of **CDK12** and **CDK13**, which disables **triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)** cells.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/?utm_source=openai))

- **Title:** SR-4835 | CDK12/13 inhibitor | Axon 3184 | Axon Medchem  
  - **URL:** `https://www.axonmedchem.com/product/3184`  
  - **Direct quote snippets:**  
    - “**SR-4835** is a… dual inhibitor of **CDK12** and **CDK13**…”  
    - “SR-4835 has… anti-**triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)** activity…” ([axonmedchem.com](https://www.axonmedchem.com/product/3184?utm_source=openai))

- **Title:** Noncovalent CDK12/13 dual inhibitors-based PROTACs… - PubMed  
  - **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/`  
  - **Direct quote snippets:**  
    - “a potent **PROTAC degrader PP-C8** based on the noncovalent dual inhibitors of **CDK12/13**…”  
    - “synergistic… effects… in **triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)**.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/?utm_source=openai))

- **Title:** PP-C8 | PROTAC CDK12-Cyclin K Degrader | MedChemExpress  
  - **URL:** `https://www.medchemexpress.eu/pp-c8.html`  
  - **Direct quote snippets:**  
    - “**PP-C8** is a potent and selective **PROTAC CDK12-Cyclin K degrader**.”  
    - “**CAS No. : 3032108-74-7**”  
    - “in **triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)**.” ([medchemexpress.eu](https://www.medchemexpress.eu/pp-c8.html?utm_source=openai))

- **Title:** Discovery of a Highly Potent and Selective Dual PROTAC Degrader of CDK12 and CDK13 - PubMed  
  - **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/`  
  - **Direct quote snippets:**  
    - “dual **CDK12/13 degraders**… The optimal compound **7f** effectively degraded **CDK12** and **CDK13**…”  
    - “inhibited proliferation of multiple **TNBC** cell lines…” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/?utm_source=openai))

- **Title:** Discovery and design of molecular glue enhancers of CDK12–DDB1 interactions for targeted degradation of cyclin K - RSC Chemical Biology  
  - **URL:** `https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2025/cb/d4cb00190g`  
  - **Direct quote snippets:**  
    - “**SR-4835** occupies the ATP-binding pocket of **CDK12** and bridges the **CDK12–DDB1** interface…”  
    - “to generate compound **MR-1226**”  
    - “**MR-1226** effectively degraded **cyclin K** with a **DC_{50} of 50 nM**” ([pubs.rsc.org](https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2025/cb/d4cb00190g?utm_source=openai))

  - **Direct quote snippets:**  
    - “**WO2019217421A1 - Small molecule inhibitors of cdk12/cdk13**”  
    - “Compounds can be used in treatment of cancers, such as **breast cancer**…” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2019217421A1/en?utm_source=openai))
